Go to your github home page. Look up your fork and select your pushed branch. Then press pull request button. Wait for the maintainer comments or you can start another feature.
Checkout your master branch and create a new branch using the ticket number and description as branch name.
As repository mantainer you've to check the proposed branches availables in the pull request section of your repository.
Check it, test it, comment it and if you like it ... merge it ;)
1. Clone your project : git clone git@github.com/openshine/osproject.git
2. Add john's git as remote : git remote add john git@github.com/john/osproject.git
3. Fetch john's git repository : git fetch john
4. Merge the proposed branch : git merge john/ticketnumber-description
6. Push to master : git push origin master
